<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>In addition to accepting XML/HTML strings, the Zend_Dom_Query constructor (and setDocument*() methods) should accept DOMDocument objects, allowing developers to use Zend_Dom_Query to query already-existing DOM objects without first converting them to strings.  E.g.,</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$domObject = new DOMDocument('1.0', 'utf-8');
$domObject-&gt;loadXML('</code></pre><div><code>
    </code><p class="first"><code>First paragraph.</code></p><code>
    </code><p class="second"><code>Second paragraph.</code></p><code>
</code></div><code>');
$queryObject = new Zend_Dom_Query($domObject);
$paragraphs = $queryObject-&gt;query('p.second');
echo $paragraphs-&gt;current()-&gt;nodeValue; // "Second paragraph."
</code>

<p>This usage would parallel the constructor of the PHP DOMXPath class.</p>

